ou%20automatically%20do%20when%20you%20walk%20or%20run%2C%20can%20help%20the%20digestive%20system%20run%20more%20smoothly%20and%20improve%20the%20movement%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Flymphatic-drainage-massage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elymphatic%20fluids%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20outdoors%20can%20also%20boost%20your%20mood%20and%20calm%20the%20nervous%20system.%20The%20adjustment%20and%20re-adjustment%20that%20the%20eyes%20and%20brain%20continually%20make%20when%20walking%20or%20running%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20improve%20parasympathetic%20nervous%20system%20activity%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20and%20a%20women%20wearing%20backpacks%20and%20walking%20on%20a%20gravel%20path%20through%20the%20woods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654eab65b788914e55547109%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20way%20of%20rucking%20is%20walking%20with%20a%20weighted%20backpack.%20%3Cp%3Eurbazon%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261a61366-9919-4168-8fba-14045def94de%5C%22%3ECarrying%20weight%20is%20good%20for%20bone%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20difference%20between%20rucking%20and%20running%20is%20the%20weight-carrying%20component.%20Walking%20with%20an%20additional%20load%20requires%20more%20work%20from%20the%20cardiovascular%20system%20and%20some%20of%20your%20muscles%20than%20unloaded%20walking%2C%20Zielinski%20said.%20So%20it%20uses%20up%20more%20energy%20and%20burns%20more%20calories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20health%20benefit%20or%20quantity%20of%20fat%20you%20lose%20from%20rucking%20and%20running%20will%20depend%20on%20factors%20like%20speed%2C%20terrain%2C%20hill%20grade%2C%20duration%2C%20and%20how%20much%20load%20you%20carry%2C%20she%20said.%20You're%20going%20to%20get%20more%20of%20a%20workout%20from%20sprinting%20up%20a%20hill%20than%20you%20would%20from%20strolling%20with%20five%20pounds%20on%20your%20back%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20carrying%20a%20load%2C%20which%20humans%20have%20done%20for%20centuries%2C%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20bone%20health%2C%20Worthington%20said.%20Applying%20force%20along%20the%20length%20of%20long%20bones%2C%20known%20as%20axial%20loading%20of%20the%20skeleton%2C%20is%20really%20great%20for%20maintaining%20bone%20and%20mass%20density%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20adding%20weight%20feels%20more%20difficult%2C%20it%20can%20create%20a%20higher%20sense%20of%20achievement%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a486695d-a055-4eef-a2c8-e0eb23647a97%5C%22%3ECardio%20won't%20help%20you%20build%20muscle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorthington%20said%20that%20neither%20exercise%20would%20have%20any%20noticeable%20impact%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-exercises-build-upper-body-muscle-short-time-gym-workout-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20muscle%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20weight%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-lifting-rep-range-rule-myth-how-train-build-muscle-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIncreasing%20muscle%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E%20requires%20three%20things%3A%20A%20calorie%20surplus%20(because%20you%20can't%20make%20something%20out%20of%20nothing)%2C%20adequate%20protein%2C%20(the%20building%20blocks%20of%20muscle%20tissue)%2C%20and%20gradually%20increasing%20workload%20over%20time%2C%20(whether%20through%20increased%20weight%20or%20mechanical%20tension)%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a28caac-16b5-4adc-9d82-5e6f8a7ce858%5C%22%3EChoose%20whatever%20you're%20likely%20to%20do%20regularly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20to%20establish%20an%20exercise%20regime%2C%20start%20slow%20and%20aim%20to%20be%20consistent%2C%20the%20experts%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20for%20people%20who%20are%20not%20exercising%2C%20starting%20with%20walking%2C%20adding%20some%20grade%2C%20and%20then%20once%20they%20kind%20of%20get%20comfortable%20with%20that%20and%20feel%20like%20that's%20not%20very%20hard%20anymore%2C%20then%20adding%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20weight%20can%20up%20the%20intensity%2C%26quot%3B%20Zielinski%20said.%20This%20might%20be%20easier%20on%20the%20joints%20than%20increasing%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorthington%20said%20to%20pick%20whichever%20you%20enjoy%20more%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20do%20regularly.%20%26quot%3BLots%20of%20different%20training%20modalities%20'work'%20%E2%80%94%20the%20biggest%20issue%20people%20have%20is%20not%20doing%20them%20for%20long%20enough%20to%20actually%20allow%20them%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frunning-vs-rucking-which-is-best-fitness-routine-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718445421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frunning-vs-rucking-which-is-best-fitness-routine-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20cardiologist%20and%20celebrity%20personal%20trainer%20said%20running%20and%20rucking%20offer%20similar%20benefits%2C%20so%20go%20with%20whichever%20one%20you%20enjoy%20more.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40businessinsider.com%20(Kim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'LS%20victory%20is%20the%20beginning'%3A%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20hails%20MVA's%20election%20win%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718444962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111018849%2Cimgsize-1339020.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fti