oping%20new%20recipes%20for%20ultra-processed%20foods%20they%20hope%20will%20be%20healthier.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20five%20years%20since%20nutrition%20scientist%20Kevin%20Hall%20made%20a%20startling%20discovery%20that%20changed%20the%20way%20we%20view%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-processed-foods-lead-to-weight-gain-nih-study-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHall%20put%2020%20people%20%E2%80%94%2010%20women%20and%2010%20men%20%E2%80%94%20into%20a%20tightly%20controlled%20metabolic%20ward%20at%20the%20National%20Institutes%20of%20Health%20and%20watched%20what%20they%20ate%20for%20a%20month.%20Half%20the%20time%2C%20the%20study%20subjects%20were%20given%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-eat-a-completely-unprocessed-food-diet-benefits-drawbacks-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efresh%2C%20unprocessed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Greek%20yogurt%20with%20fruit%20and%20nuts%20for%20breakfast%2C%20or%20a%20broccoli%20and%20beef%20stir-fry%20for%20dinner.%20For%20the%20other%20half%20of%20the%20month%2C%20they%20were%20offered%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20calories%20and%20key%20nutrients%20every%20day%2C%20but%20from%20factory%20foods%20like%20turkey%20bacon%2C%20English%20muffins%2C%20and%20chicken%20nuggets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kevin%20hall%20talking%20to%20study%20participant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666bb9bf764df1611259ce55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22446%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20Kevin%20Hall%2C%20center%2C%20and%20Stephanie%20Chung%2C%20right%2C%20talk%20with%20a%20study%20participant.%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Rymaruk%2C%20NIDDK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20the%20evidence%20was%20conclusive%20and%20damning%3A%20people%20who%20eat%20ultra-processed%20diets%20consume%20more%20calories%2C%20and%20gain%20more%20weight%2C%20without%20trying.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20randomized%20controlled%20study%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20and%20it%20changed%20the%20way%20we%20view%20ultra-processed%20foods.%20%26quot%3BWhole%26quot%3B%20food%20and%20%26quot%3Bplant-based%26quot%3B%20diets%20took%20off%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20eating%20has%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scrippsnews.com%2Fscience-and-tech%2Fsocial-media%2Fhow-social-media-has-fueled-clean-eating-movement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrendier%20than%20ever%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20people%20try%20to%20aggressively%20limit%20their%20intake%20of%20packaged%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20discovering%20that%20people%20eat%20about%20500%20extra%20calories%20per%20day%20on%20an%20ultra-processed%20diet%20didn't%20convince%20Hall%20that%20convenience%20foods%20should%20be%20universally%20shunned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20is%2C%20very%20specifically%2C%20what%20is%20it%20about%20ultra-processed%20foods%20that%20seems%20to%20drive%20over-consumption%20and%20weight%20gain%3F%26quot%3B%20Hall%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Burger%20with%20American%20cheese%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662f7f72ec0c696569fe8edb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUltra-processed%20foods%20make%20up%2073%25%20of%20the%20US%20food%20supply.%3Cp%3EAleksandr%20Zubkov%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wants%20to%20understand%20precisely%20why%20ultra-processed%20foods%20do%20what%20they%20do%20and%20what%E2%80%94if%20anything%E2%80%94we%20can%20do%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-ultra-processed-foods-may-be-healthier-than-homemade-scientist-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20them%20healthier%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20avoid%20them%2C%20that's%20wonderful%2C%20but%20most%20people%20can't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20for%20over%20a%20year%20now%2C%20he's%20methodically%20invited%2018%20volunteers%20back%20to%20his%20special%20Bethesda%2C%20Maryland%20lab%2C%20to%20try%20out%20some%20newly%20formulated%20ultra-processed%20meals.%20By%20the%20time%20the%20study's%20over%2C%20in%202025%2C%20at%20least%2036%20people%20will%20have%20tried%20out%20the%20reformulated%20foods%2C%20and%20been%20monitored%20for%20weight%20gain%2C%20as%20well%20as%20hormonal%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHall's%20testing%20out%20two%20big%20ideas%2C%20hoping%20that%20perhaps%20by%20baking%20some%20more%20of%20the%20bedrock%20concepts%20of%20nutrition%20science%20into%20ultra-processed%20eating%2C%20we'll%20be%20able%20to%20get%20smarter%20about%20our%20ultra-processed%20existence%20and%20make%20on-the-go%20eating%20healthier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2285e3313a-4ac3-4cfe-a3d2-ddf4bf322bbe%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUltra-processed%20foods%20attack%20our%20brains%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20staring%20at%20chocolate%20cake%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666bb57ae07904901818fe0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Bradbury%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20known%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-processed-food-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%20are%20associated%20with%20all%20kinds%20of%20bad%20health%20outcomes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20more%20early%20death%2C%20to%20extra%20strokes%2C%20and%20additional%20heart%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20we%20know%20that%20refined%20carbohydrates%20(white%20bread%2C%20sugar)%2C%20syrupy%20beverages%20(soda%2C%20juice)%2C%20and%20ultra-processed%20meats%20(hot%20dogs)%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-linked-early-death-study-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20of%20the%20most%20dangerous%20foods%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whether%20the%20entire%20category%20%E2%80%94%20all%20packaged%2C%20ultra-processed%20foods%20are%20inherently%20bad%20for%20us%20by%20nature%20%E2%80%94%20is%20still%20an%20open%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20characteristic%20that%20separates%20many%20ultra-processed%20foods%20from%20their%20unprocessed%20counterparts%20is%20the%20calorie%20density.%20Each%20bite%20of%20an%20ultra-processed%20meal%20tends%20to%20have%20more%20calories%20in%20it%2C%20without%20nearly%20as%20much%20fiber%20as%20fresh%20fare.%20That%20may%20be%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20ultra-processed%20diets%20can%20lead%20to%20overeating%2C%20Hall%20said%3A%20simply%20because%20each%20bite%20is%20rich%20and%20high-fat%2C%20yet%20not%20very%20satiating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22fresh%20salad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666bb61c764df1611259cda2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFresh%20veggies%20tend%20to%20be%20high-volume%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20low%20in%20calories%2C%20and%20slow%20to%20digest%2C%20helping%20people%20feel%20full.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHall's%20second%20big%20hypothesis%20is%20that%20ultra-processed%20foods%20might%20drive%20people%20to%20eat%20more%20because%20they're%20%26quot%3Bhyper-palatable%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20they're%20rich%20in%20tantalizing%20combinations%20of%20fat%20and%20salt%2C%20or%20fat%20and%20sugar%2C%20or%20carbohydrates%20and%20salt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20nothing%20in%20nature%20tastes%20that%20good%20to%20us%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20only%20natural%20%26quot%3Bhyper-palatable%26quot%3B%20foods%20is%20a%20mother's%20breast%20milk.%20%26quot%3BBreast%20milk%20can%20be%20sweet%20and%20fatty%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20said.%20We%20may%20be%20evolutionarily%20attuned%20to%20find%20these%20rarer%20types%20of%20composed%20foods%20irresistible%2C%20a%20hard-wired%20survival%20instinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20cook%20from%20scratch%2C%20it's%20near-impossible%20to%20include%20as%20much%20sodium%20and%20fat%20as%20factories%20do%20when%20fusing%20together%20ultra-processed%20foods.%20At%20home%2C%20combo%20dishes%20can%20still%20be%20hyper-palatable%2C%20but%20sugar%20and%20oils%20tend%20to%20bump%20up%20against%20watery%20vegetables%20and%20grains.%20In%20Hall's%20landmark%202019%20study%2C%20only%20about%2040%25%20of%20the%20foods%20on%20the%20unprocessed%20diet%20were%20hyper-palatable%2C%20while%20roughly%2070%25%20of%20the%20foods%20on%20the%20ultra-processed%20diet%20were%20composed%20of%20these%20particularly%20%26quot%3Bhyper-palatable%26quot%3B%20high%20ratios%20of%20salt%2C%20sugar%2C%20fat%2C%20and%20carbohydrates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20easiest%2C%20cheapest%2C%20quickest%20dinner%20option%20involves%20filling%20your%20plate%20with%20mouth-wateringly%20delicious%20but%20low-nutrition%20fare%2C%20that's%20exactly%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20do.%20The%20question%20is%3A%20can%20we%20do%20anything%20to%20make%20hyper-palatable%20foods%20a%20little%20less%20damaging%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cba1a38-2332-4897-8abf-4fc3c108bb0f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20the%20composition%20of%20your%20plate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hummus%20platter%20with%20carrots%20and%20celery%20and%20pits%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60c3af5e6d855e0018157a3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20lab%20is%20experimenting%20with%20adding%20more%20veggies%20into%20ultra-processed%20meals.%20%3Cp%3Efcafotodigital%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20new%20experiment%2C%20Hall%20is%20trying%20out%20a%20few%20different%20techniques%20to%20study%20where%20the%20link%20exists%20between%20ultra-processing%20and%20weight%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20idea%3A%20cutting%20back%20on%20%26quot%3Bhyper-palatable%26quot%3B%20foods%20in%20some%20ultra-processed%20meals.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20participants%20may%20still%20consume%20more%20calories%20in%20each%20bite%20than%20they%20would%20when%20eating%20an%20unprocessed%20meal%2C%20they'll%20(perhaps)%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20overeat%2C%20since%20the%20foods%20won't%20be%20as%20irresistible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20idea%20is%20to%20cut%20calories%20by%20simply%20adding%20some%20non-starchy%20vegetables%20to%20a%20plate%20of%20ultra-processed%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20end%20up%20with%20more%20salads%2C%20for%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20adding%20a%20side%20of%20veggies%20to%20a%20convenience%20meal%20ends%20up%20normalizing%20how%20many%20calories%20people%20eat%2C%20that%20could%20change%20the%20way%20we%20think%20about%20how%20we%20choose%20processed%20foods%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20the%20way%20that%20manufacturers%20make%20them%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20want%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22776bbf74-2585-4706-b6b6-00d4194201d3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20fast%20food%20ever%20be%20healthy%20food%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20cutting%20vegetables%20at%20NIH%20kitchen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666bb962e07904901818fee7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22509%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chef%20at%20the%20National%20Institutes%20of%20Health's%20metabolic%20kitchen.%20The%20NIH%20precisely%20measures%20the%20amount%20of%20key%20nutrients%20that%20are%20available%20in%20each%20meal%2C%20matching%20ultra-processed%20to%20unprocessed%20offerings.%20But%20it's%20up%20to%20participants%20to%20decide%20what%20they%20want%20to%20eat%2C%20and%20how%20much.%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Rymaruk%2C%20NIDDK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHall%20has%20a%20more%20surgical%20technique%20he's%20trying%20out%20in%20the%20experiment%2C%20too.%20He's%20dissolving%20fiber%20supplements%20into%20some%20of%20the%20ultra-processed%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20stirring%20fiber%20powder%20into%20packaged%20yogurts%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20to%20see%20if%20that%20curbs%20overeating%20and%20improves%20health%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20more%20straightfoward%20idea%2C%20and%20one%20that%20could%20be%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20food%20manufacturing%20industry%20if%20it%20shows%20promise.(Already%2C%20big%20food%20companies%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nestle.com%2Fmedia%2Fnews%2Fvital-pursuit-brand-glp-1-weight-support%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENestle%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20refomulating%20some%20packaged%20foods%20like%20frozen%20pizzas%20to%20include%20more%20fiber%20and%20protein%2C%20targeting%20patients%20on%20appetite-supressing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-glp-1-drugs-ozempic-wegovy-mounjaro-effects-future-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGLP-1%20drugs%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Ozempic.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20ultra-processed%20foods%20can%20actually%20be%20reformulated%20for%20health%2C%20I%20imagine%20something%20more%20idyllic%20than%20just%20some%20extra%20fiber%20sprinkled%20into%20frozen%20pizzas%20and%20yogurts.%20What%20about%20aisles%20of%20packaged%20goods%20with%20more%20beans%2C%20nuts%2C%20seeds%2C%20and%20less%20sugar%20in%20them%20than%20before%3F%20UPFs%20could%20also%20take%20a%20nod%20from%20traditional%20diets%20that%20we%20know%20work%20well%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterranean-diet-snacks-to-cut-back-on-processed-foods-dietitian-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMediterranean%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20rich%20in%20olive%20oil%2C%20lentils%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthy-blue-zone-vegan-chicken-salad-recipe-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echickpeas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20citrus%2C%20which%20are%20all%20relatively%20shelf-stable%20items%20that%20experts%20agree%20are%20good%20for%20your%20heart%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-longevity-supplements-vs-exercise-and-diet-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20longevity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20could%20eat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-zone-frozen-meals-tasty-healthy-expensive-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erice%20and%20beans%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20a%20bag%2C%20or%20enjoy%20a%20side%20of%20vacuum-packed%20veggies%2C%20instead%20of%20potato%20chips.%20Those%20would%20be%20more%20health-forward%20choices%20than%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplant-based-upf-processed-linked-heart-disease-death-study-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bplant-based%26quot%3B%20treat%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20a%20high-fat%20pastry%2C%20no%20matter%20whether%20it%20is%20homemade%20or%20factory-built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20yogurt%20parfait%20in%20a%20jar%20with%20berries%20and%20granola.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661989301caec1275a6fbbfa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWill%20mixing%20powdered%20fiber%20into%20packaged%20yogurts%20help%3F%20%3Cp%3EArx0nt%2FGetty%20images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20things%20that%20we've%20known%20about%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20are%20still%20worth%20taking%20into%20consideration%2C%20Hall%20says%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20processed%20your%20diet%20is.%20Seek%20out%20nuts%2C%20seeds%2C%20whole%20grains%20like%20oats%20or%20quinoa%2C%20black%20beans%2C%20hummus%2C%20lentils%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20yes%20%E2%80%94%20unprocessed%20fresh%20veggies%20and%20fruit%20when%20you%20can.%20Avoid%20sugary%20snacks%20and%20refined%20grains.%20These%20are%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20things%20that%20the%20dietary%20guidelines%20already%20discuss%20ad%20nauseam.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-making-ultra-processed-foods-healthier-in-major-new-study-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718444581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666a1088764df16112594b58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-making-ultra-processed-foods-healthier-in-major-new-study-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20nutrition%20scientist%20is%20reformulating%20ultra-processed%20foods%2C%20hoping%20to%20develop%20healthier%20alternatives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-making-ultra-processed-foods-healthier-in-major-new-study-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20York%20City%20briefly%20opened%20its%20housing%20voucher%20waitlist.%20But%20getting%20that%20assistance%20is%20as%20unlikely%20as%20getting%20into%20Harvard.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Looking%20east%20from%20the%20Hudson%20River%20in%20Riverside%20Park%20past%20the%20West%20Side%20Highway%20are%20high%20rises%20on%20the%20upper%20west%20side%20in%20Manhattan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666a1196ed9a404d829d34ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDeb%20Cohn-Orbach%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20York%20City%20received%20over%20630%2C000%20applications%20to%20join%20its%20waitlist%20for%20federal%20housing%20vouchers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20city%20will%20issue%20just%2020%2C000%20new%20vouchers%2C%20amid%20a%20severe%20housing%20affordability%20crisis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20third%20of%20New%20Yorkers%20spend%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20an%20affordable%20apartment%20in%20New%20York%20City%20has%20become%20ever%20more%20challenging%20for%20low-income%20people%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20an%20expansion%20of%20key%20federal%20assistance%20isn't%20likely%20to%20help%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20city%20opened%20its%20waitlist%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-vouchers-crisis-funding-landlords-restrictions-inspections-renters-struggle-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20choice%20vouchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2015%20years%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20it%20was%20flooded%20with%20more%20than%20630%2C000%20applications%20for%20the%20federal%20rental%20assistance%20program%2C%20Gothamist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgothamist.com%2Fnews%2F1-week-633000-applications-for-section-8-in-nyc-what-comes-next%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnewyork%2Fnews%2Fnyc-section-8-application-what-to-know%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeligible%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20individuals%20can%20make%20no%20more%20than%20%2454%2C350%20a%20year%2C%20and%20families%20of%20four%20can't%20make%20more%20than%20%2477%2C650.%20But%20the%20city%20is%20capping%20the%20waitlist%20at%20200%2C000%20applicants%2C%20selected%20randomly.%20Ultimately%2C%20though%2C%20it%20will%20only%20issue%2020%2C000%20new%20vouchers%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20number%20of%20vouchers%20up%20from%20about%2096%2C000%20to%20about%20115%2C000%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nysenate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Farticles%2F2024%2Fliz-krueger%2Fnychas-section-8-waitlist-reopening%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20New%20York%20City%20Housing%20Authority%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20won't%20happen%20overnight%20%E2%80%94%20the%20vouchers%20will%20be%20issued%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20about%201%2C000%20a%20month.%20And%20those%20on%20the%20waitlist%20have%20to%20reapply%20every%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20just%20over%203%25%20of%20those%20who've%20applied%20to%20be%20on%20the%20waitlist%20will%20end%20up%20snagging%20one%20of%20those%2020%2C000%20additional%20vouchers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0about%20the%20same%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usnews.com%2Fbest-colleges%2Fharvard-university-2155%2Fapplying%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHarvard%2520University%2520has%2520an%2520acceptance%2Cquarter%2520scored%2520below%2520these%2520ranges.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epercentage%20who%20get%20accepted%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Harvard%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%20has%20the%20largest%20housing%20voucher%20program%20in%20the%20country%2C%20but%20it%20still%20falls%20far%20short%20of%20need.%20Rents%20and%20home%20prices%20have%20skyrocketed%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20increasing%20numbers%20of%20New%20Yorkers%20can%20no%20longer%20afford%20housing.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20New%20York%20City%20tenants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fstateofthecity%2Fview%2Fstate-of-renters-and-their-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20rent-burdened%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20they%20spend%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent%2C%20and%20a%20third%20of%20New%20Yorkers%20spend%20more%20than%20half%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20this%20isn't%20just%20a%20New%20York%20problem.%20Communities%20all%20across%20the%20country%20are%20facing%20severe%20housing%20affordability%20crises%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-vouchers-crisis-funding-landlords-restrictions-inspections-renters-struggle-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20sufficient%20vouchers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Half%20of%20renters%20across%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freports%2Ffiles%2FHarvard_JCHS_Americas_Rental_Housing_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20rent-burdened%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22477c384d-b7e4-4141-8b55-7059aa22cc2a%5C%22%3EA%20flawed%20system%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20vouchers%20are%20the%20biggest%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbpp.org%2Fblog%2Fmaking-rental-assistance-work-better-for-people-struggling-to-afford-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emost%20effective%20housing%20assistance%20program%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country.%20They%20help%20about%205%20million%20people%20afford%20their%20rent%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20lots%20of%20evidence%20that%20vouchers%20effectively%20lower%20the%20risk%20of%20homelessness%2C%20reduce%20dangerous%20housing%20conditions%20like%20overcrowding%2C%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fpublication%2Fdo-housing-vouchers-improve-academic-performance-evidence-from-new-york-cit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelp%20kids%20do%20better%20in%20school%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20they%20significantly%20lower%20recipients'%20rent%20burden.%20Voucher%20holders%20pay%20about%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20toward%20rent%2C%20while%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%20covers%20the%20rest%20%E2%80%94%20up%20to%20what%20it%20determines%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20hre