%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20older%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20geriatric%20Americans%20are%20holding%20more%20power%20than%20ever%20before.%20So%2C%20to%20parse%20out%20how%20millionaires%20stack%20up%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20population%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20age%20breakdowns%20in%20both%201992%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20the%20general%20population%20%E2%80%94%20and%20millionaires%20%E2%80%94%20looked%20like%20in%201992.%20Millionaires%20are%20overrepresented%20beginning%20around%20age%2050%2C%20but%20track%20pretty%20cleanly%20with%20the%20cohort%20in%20their%2040's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FnB8D8%2F4%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Age%20distribution%20for%20everyone%20vs.%20millionaires%20in%201992%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EComparatively%2C%20millionaires%20were%20more%20overrepresented%20in%20the%2060%2B%20cohort%20as%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fqmlcx%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Age%20distribution%20for%20everyone%20vs.%20millionaires%20in%202022%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22653%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20millionaires%20with%20net%20worths%20of%20more%20than%20%241%20million%2C%20Americans%20who%20make%20an%20annual%20salary%20of%20%241%20million%20are%20also%20skewing%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarrett%20Watson%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20Tax%20Foundation%2C%20analyzed%20IRS%20SOI%20data%20and%20found%20that%20in%202011%2C%20about%2059%2C500%20Americans%2065%20and%20over%20reported