ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc9xxklr0070o%233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Afghan%20women%20tell%20the%20BBC%20they%20were%20beaten%20and%20tortured%20for%20protesting%20against%20the%20Taliban.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A71%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc9xxklr0070o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc9xxklr0070o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc9xxklr0070o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20happened%20to%20the%20women%20who%20took%20on%20the%20Taliban%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718402357000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.ukundefined%2F%233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Afghan%20women%20tell%20the%20BBC%20they%20were%20beaten%20and%20tortured%20for%20protesting%20against%20the%20Taliban.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%228%20ways%20to%20give%20your%20grandkids%20money%20without%20sacrificing%20your%20retirement%20savings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-give-grandkids-money-without-sacrificing-retirement-savings-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaid%20non-client%20promotion%3A%20Affiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting-rating-methodology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20investing%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221990%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22grandfather%20and%20grandchild%20grandson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e5572d4fee23d3cdc05a988%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22995%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKlaus%20Vedfelt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESupporting%20your%20grandkids%20shouldn't%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20your%20own%20comfort%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EConsidering%20contributing%20to%20a%20529%20plan%20for%20their%20college%20education%2C%20or%20making%20them%20your%20life%20insurance%20beneficiary.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20also%20write%20them%20into%20your%20will%2C%20or%20set%20up%20a%20trust%20fund%20to%20handle%20the%20doling%20out%20of%20assets.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOffering%20financial%20support%20to%20a%20grandchild%20can%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20rewarding%20parts%20of%20being%20a%20grandparent.%20But%20when%20that%20generosity%20comes%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20depleting%20your%20own%20retirement%20savings%2C%20the%20prospect%20becomes%20a%20lot%20less%20compelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20such%20an%20either%2For%20proposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHappily%2C%20a%20little%20research%20yields%20%3Cem%3Eplenty%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20creative%20ways%20to%20provide%20for%20the%20next%20generation%20beyond%20dipping%20into%20your%20own%20hard-earned%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alternatives%20include%20everything%20from%20special%20investment%20strategies%20to%20estate%20planning%20to%20savings%20plans%20that%20let%20you%20save%20for%20your%20loved%20ones%20on%20your%20terms.%20In%20short%2C%20there's%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20options%20that%20make%20the%20ability%20to%20help%20out%20a%20family%20member%20feel%20like%20a%20positive%20again%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20mandate%20to%20sacrifice%20your%20own%20comfort%20and%20stability%20for%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegacy%20Financial%20Advisors'%20Kathryn%20Amorello%20has%20several%20suggestions%20for%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20support%20your%20grandkids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Contribute%20to%20a%20529%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20know%20that%20you%20specifically%20want%20to%20support%20your%20grandchild's%20education%2C%20there's%20no%20better%20way%20to%20make%20that%20happen%20than%20by%20investing%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-529-plan%5C%22%3E529%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Named%20after%20the%20section%20of%20the%20Internal%20Revenue%20Code%20that%20authorizes%20them%2C%20a%20529%20is%20an%20investment%20account%20that%20allows%20your%20money%20to%20both%20grow%20and%20be%20withdrawn%20tax-free.%20(So%20long%20as%20it's%20used%20to%20cover%20college%20expenses%20like%20tuition%2C%20board%2C%20books%2C%20and%20other%20necessary%20supplies.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plans%20are%20state-sponsored%2C%20meaning%20your%20area%20will%20have%20its%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F529-college-savings-plans-by-state%5C%22%3Eunique%20options%20and%20investment%20structures%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20the%20majority%20of%20states%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20529%20will%20earn%20you%20a%20deduction%20on%20your%20taxes%2C%20and%20annual%20contribution%20limits%20are%20often%20quite%20high.%20(They%20begin%20at%20%24235%2C000%20for%20some%20states.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20any%20contribution%20to%20a%20529%20is%20considered%20a%20%26quot%3Bgift%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%2C%20so%20those%20hoping%20to%20avoid%20the%20gift%20tax%20will%20want%20to%20keep%20their%20contributions%20under%20%2417%2C000%20a%20year.%20(Setting%20up%20automatic%20monthly%20deposits%20means%20your%20money%20can%20grow%20out%20of%20sight%20and%20out%20of%20mind.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20if%20you%20have%20the%20funds%20available%20and%20you%20prefer%2C%20you%20can%20deposit%20a%20lump%20sum%20upon%20opening%20the%20account%3B%20you%20just%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20contribute%20again%20for%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmorello%20is%20a%20particular%20proponent%20of%20the%20529%20plan%20for%20its%20flexibility%2C%20noting%2C%20%26quot%3BContributing%20to%20a%20529%20Age-Based%20Investment%20Strategy%20gives%20the%20grandparents%20options%20on%20how%20conservative%2C%20moderate%2C%20or%20aggressive%20fund%20choices%20should%20be.%20As%20the%20child%20nears%20college%20age%2C%20the%20balance%20of%20investments%20transitions%20appropriately%2C%20from%20more%20stocks%20to%20more%20bonds%2C%20in%20order%20to%20help%20your%20funds%20grow%20predictably.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20that%20flexibility%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20anyone%20can%20contribute%20to%20the%20account%20and%20that%20even%20if%20the%20original%20beneficiary%20elects%20not%20to%20go%20to%20college%20or%20selects%20a%20cheaper%20option%20than%20predicted%2C%20the%20beneficiary%20can%20be%20reassigned%20in%20order%20to%20use%20up%20the%20remaining%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Write%20them%20into%20your%20will%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20about%20unexpected%20expenses%20is%20that%20there's%20absolutely%20no%20way%20to%20predict%20when%20they'll%20crop%20up.%20So%2C%20one%20way%20to%20make%20absolutely%20certain%20that%20you%20won't%20end%20up%20needing%20the%20funds%20that%20you%20set%20aside%20for%20your%20grandchildren%20is%20to%20write%20them%20into%20your%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20you'll%20know%20you've%20truly%20set%20aside%20all%20you%20safely%20can%20for%20your%20grandchildren%20without%20having%20to%20grapple%20with%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20medical%20event%20or%20stress%20about%20the%20penalty%20for%20an%20unplanned%20withdrawal%20from%2C%20say%2C%20a%20529%20plan%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20like%20they%20say%20on%20airplanes%3A%20Put%20on%20your%20own%20oxygen%20mask%20before%20attempting%20to%20help%20anyone%20else.%20If%20you%20run%20out%20of%20retirement%20money%20during%20the%20course%20of%20your%20life%2C%20it%20doesn't%20help%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20least%20of%20all%20your%20grandchildren.%20This%20is%20the%20money%20that%20you%20saved%20for%20your%20retirement%2C%20so%20leaving%20instructions%20for%20its%20disbursal%20in%20your%20will%20ensures%20that%20you%20meet%20that%20goal%20before%20setting%20another%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Make%20them%20your%20life%20insurance%20beneficiary%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20same%20lines%20as%20recognizing%20a%20grandchild%20in%20your%20will%2C%20you%20can%20also%20assign%20a%20grandchild%20as%20your%20life%20insurance%20beneficiary%2C%20meaning%20they%20would%20be%20the%20one%20to%20receive%20the%20payout%20from%20your%20insurance%20company%20in%20the%20event%20of%20your%20death%20during%20the%20covered%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20many%20companies%20let%20you%20list%20multiple%20beneficiaries%20who%20can%20either%20divide%20the%20payout%20evenly%20or%20receive%20specific%20percentages%20that%20you%20set%20yourself.%20It's%20also%20easy%20for%20you%20to%20redesignate%20the%20beneficiary%2C%20should%20circumstances%20change%20somehow%2C%20and%20you%20can%20even%20specify%20a%20%3Cem%3Econtingent%3C%2Fem%3E%20beneficiary%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20second%20choice%20to%20receive%20the%20payout%2C%20should%20your%20first%20choice%20be%20unavailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20designate%20a%20beneficiary%2C%20however%2C%20the%20payout%20will%20be%20added%20to%20your%20estate%2C%20which%20opens%20it%20up%20to%20being%20argued%20over%20by%20creditors%20and%20lenders.%20And%20since%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20paying%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Elife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20policy%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20loved%20ones%20are%20financially%20provided%20for%20in%20your%20absence%2C%20setting%20a%20grandchild%20as%20your%20policy's%20beneficiary%20is%20a%20no-brainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Arrange%20to%20cover%20your%20estate%20taxes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20insurance%2C%20if%20you're%20a%20high%20earner%20whose%20estate%20is%20going%20to%20qualify%20for%20estate%20taxes%2C%20Amorello%20suggests%20taking%20out%20an%20insurance%20policy%20where%20the%20funds%20are%20specified%20to%20pay%20off%20those%20taxes.%20%26quot%3BThat%20way%2C%20it's%20no%20imposition%20on%20a%20child%20or%20grandchild's%20actual%20inheritance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20current%20levels%2C%20most%20American%20families%20will%20have%20absolutely%20zero%20interaction%20with%20federal%20estate%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20states%20have%20their%20own%20estate%20and%20inheritance%20taxes%2C%20and%20the%20federal%20exemptions%20are%20fluid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20your%20insurance%20is%20%3Cem%3Efor%20you%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20so%20make%20sure%20you're%20selecting%20a%20policy%20with%20fine%20print%20and%20riders%20that%20make%20it%20work%20that%20way%3A%20as%20a%20cushion%20between%20your%20loved%20ones%20and%20financial%20hardship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Gift%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20way%20to%20balance%20out%20potential%20estate%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20can%20be%20as%20high%20as%2040%25%20%E2%80%94%20is%20by%20gifting%20money%20to%20your%20grandchildren%20during%20your%20lifetime.%20Amorello%20explained%3A%20%26quot%3BGifting%20money%20actually%20can%20help%20grandparents%20lessen%20their%20own%20net%20worth%20to%20lower%20estate%20taxes.%20Because%20if%20you're%20leaving%20behind%20an%20inheritance%2C%20but%20half%20of%20it%20is%20going%20to%20the%20estate%20taxes%2C%20that%20can%20be%20a%20daunting%20realization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20emphasized%20that%20if%20you%20take%20this%20option%2C%20it's%20crucial%20to%20work%20within%20federal%20limits%2C%20as%20gifts%20exceeding%20%2415%2C000%20per%20grandchild%20per%20year%20will%20incur%20the%20gift%20tax.%20(The%20donor%20pays%20this%20tax%2C%20and%20it%20is%20probably%20not%20the%20way%20you%20want%20your%20retirement%20savings%20eaten%20up.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eare%3C%2Fem%3E%20some%20exemptions%20to%20gift%20tax%20law%3A%20Monetary%20gifts%20in%20excess%20of%20%2417%2C000%20can%20remain%20tax-free%20as%20long%20as%20they%20go%20toward%20medical%20or%20educational%20expenses%20and%20are%20paid%20directly%20to%20the%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Do%20your%20research%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20fail-safe%20way%20to%20help%20out%20your%20grandchildren%20across%20the%20board%20is%20by%20staying%20up%20to%20date%20on%20any%20changes%20to%20the%20law%20that%20will%20affect%20inheritances.%20One%20recent%20change%20that%20Amorello%20highlighted%20is%20buried%20within%20the%20Secure%20Act%2C%20which%20passed%20in%20December%202019%20and%20is%20intended%20to%20help%20Americans%20save%20more%20and%20save%20%3Cem%3Ebetter%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20probably%20already%20aware%20that%20the%20bill%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20small%20business%20owners%20to%20offer%20retirement%20plans%20and%20raised%20the%20required%20minimum%20distribution%20age%20from%2070%201%2F2%20to%2072%2C%20but%20you%20might%20not%20have%20noticed%20one%20provision%20affecting%20what's%20called%20the%20stretch%20IRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeneficiaries%20of%20IRAs%20used%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20income%20from%20an%20inherited%20IRA%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20lifetime%2C%20but%20now%20there%20is%20a%2010-year%20limit%2C%26quot%3B%20Amorello%20explained.%20Under%20the%20new%20law%2C%20anyone%20who%20inherits%20an%20IRA%20will%20have%20to%20empty%20it%20within%2010%20years%20of%20the%20death%20of%20the%20original%20account%20holder%2C%20devastating%20its%20growth%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Amorello%20noted%2C%20changes%20like%20this%20one%20affect%20income%20and%20estate%20planning%20across%20the%20board%2C%20so%20keeping%20abreast%20of%20them%20now%20can%20help%20your%20family%20avoid%20a%20scramble%20of%20research%20and%20fact-finding%20during%20what%20will%20already%20be%20a%20traumatic%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20Consider%20a%20trust%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you've%20mentally%20ruled%20out%20a%20trust%20fund%2C%20assuming%20they're%20just%20for%20the%20ultrarich%2C%20but%20trust%20funds%20are%20actually%20an%20option%20well%20worth%20considering%2C%20no%20matter%20your%20income%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20heart%2C%20a%20trust%20fund%20is%20an%20account%20that%20gives%20the%20grantor%20control%20over%20how%20and%20to%20whom%20it%20pays%20out.%20Many%20do%20require%20fees%20to%20run%2C%20and%20in%20order%20to%20formally%20set%20one%20up%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20meet%20with%20(and%20yes%2C%20pay)%20an%20estate%20attorney.%20But%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20what%20you're%20paying%20for%20is%20the%20assurance%20that%20your%20intentions%20for%20your%20assets%20will%20be%20followed%20to%20the%20letter%20even%20after%20your%20death%2C%20and%20that%20peace%20of%20mind%20is%20priceless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20a%20trust%20fund%20is%20a%20legal%20way%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20defer%20%E2%80%94%20taxes%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20stocked%20with%20a%20whole%20range%20of%20assets%2C%20including%20real%20estate%2C%20business%20interests%2C%20and%20even%20life%20insurance%20policies.%20In%20essence%2C%20it's%20a%20way%20of%20consolidating%20those%20assets%20and%20moving%20them%20to%20heirs%20swiftly%20and%20efficiently%20without%20getting%20the%20whole%20process%20tangled%20up%20in%20the%20red%20tape%20of%20the%20probate%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmorello%20specifically%20recommends%20a%20trust%20for%20situations%20where%20a%20gradual%20payout%20over%20time%20might%20be%20more%20ideal%20than%20a%20lump-sum%20inheritance%2C%20like%20for%20a%20grandchild%20who%20has%20struggled%20with%20money%20management%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20good%20trust%20can%20be%20very%20specific%20about%20who%20gets%20what%2C%20when%20they%20get%20it%2C%20and%20how%20much%20they%20can%20have%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20advised.%20Much%20like%20crafting%20a%20will%2C%20building%20a%20trust%20gives%20you%20the%20ability%20to%20set%20your%20own%20terms%20for%20the%20eventual%20payout%2C%20choosing%20language%20that%20has%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20both%20you%20and%20your%20grandchild%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E8.%20Introduce%20your%20grandchild%20to%20your%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20the%20saying%20about%20giving%20a%20man%20a%20fish%20versus%20teaching%20him%20to%20fish%3F%20Nowhere%20is%20it%20better%20applied%20than%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20building%20solid%20money%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntroduce%20your%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Eyour%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20them%20help%20with%20saving%20and%20planning%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Amorello%20urged.%20%26quot%3BA%20good%2C%20family-based%20practice%20works%20with%20all%20generations%20to%20set%20everyone%20up%20for%20success.%20The%20younger%20you%20are%20when%20you%20start%20working%20with%20an%20adviser%2C%20the%20better%20off%20you'll%20be%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20Especially%20if%20you%20are%20planning%20on%20leaving%20behind%20a%20large%20inheritance%2C%20having%20a%20professional%20guiding%20your%20grandchildren%20toward%20prudent%20investment%20strategies%20can%20help%20grow%20the%20funds%20during%20a%20time%20in%20their%20life%20where%20they%20likely%20don't%20yet%20need%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20schools%20are%20woefully%20lacking%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20teaching%20kids%20about%20money%20management%2C%20so%20tackling%20that%20task%20yourself%20will%20likely%20prove%20indispensable%20to%20your%20family's%20future%20financial%20health.%20Plus%2C%20while%20advisors%20will%20take%20a%20small%20fee%20based%20on%20client%20needs%2C%20Amorello%20noted%20that%20most%20firms%20will%20take%20that%20fee%20from%20the%20grandparents%20%E2%80%94%20the%20existing%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20to%20start%2C%20turning%20this%20invaluable%20learning%20opportunity%20into%20even%20more%20of%20a%20gift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20ultimately%2C%20isn't%20that%20what%20this%20is%20all%20about%3F%20Being%20able%20to%20provide%20financial%20support%20to%20a%20grandchild%20should%20feel%20like%20a%20gift%2C%20because%20it%20is.%20By%20implementing%20the%20suggestions%20on%20this%20list%2C%20you%20can%20help%20ensure%20that%20that%20gift%20goes%20both%20ways.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3Dbipfi_give_money_retirement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20h